            "name": "dwipendra singh"
          },
          "datePublished": "2022-02-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Worst CBSE School in Hinjewadi , not even deserve single star.\nPrincipal keeps on changing every year , good teacher does not stay for longer period just because of leadership. As parents we might get  influence to see football ground but I don't think so we send our kids for sports if that's the  priority then I would prefer to choose sports school or professional academy separately.\n\nPandemic is all most over. We  all are aware  that most of school are  physically operational because  they were well prepared in advance , but as parents I am really disappointed now  that alard  could not  open because they don't have sufficient number of teachers in school and board student are suffering  because of all these  even though students are willing to go to school.\n\nToday , I came to know that school is running without principal.  I am too much worried now for son's future.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
